OL,3,CWhy the inflation fall may be bad news
OL,4,Cfor benefit recipients
OL,6,FThe 1.7% inflation figure will be a
OL,7,Fpolitical headache for the Treasury
OL,8,Fand the government, because it means
OL,9,Fbenefit payments will rise next spring
OL,10,Fby less - possibly significantly less
OL,11,F- than cost-of-living rises for those
OL,12,Fon low incomes, which are largely
OL,13,Fabout energy and food.
OL,15,FToday's fall in inflation to well
OL,16,Fbelow the 2% target is due to airfares
OL,17,Fand motor fuels, which are of less
OL,18,Frelevance to those on low incomes.
